Muhesi Airport is quite safe to seek shelter during times of distress. Muhesi Airport is a small airport in Singida, Tanzania. The airport is located at latitude -6.13925 and longitude 34.46334. The airport has one runway: 9/27. This airport has no ICAO code, we use TZ-0107 as reference. Nearby other airfields are Kilumbi Airport, Manyoni Airport, Manyoni North Airport, Mahaka Airport and Kilimatinde Airport.  Muhesi Airport does not publish a METAR, the nearest weather station is Nairobi Wilson Airport, which is 596 km away. The flight information region (FIR) is Dar Es Salaam.

An interesting feature, especially for Dar es Salaam, would be to have markers for endangered buildings (set out for demolition). Residents have shared their concerns with loss of identity, quality of life and infrastructure overcapacities related to demolitions and building of new high-rises. City council and other planning bodies (e.g. National Housing Corporation) release little to no official information about the topic and demolitions usually take place over the weekend, when courts cannot be summoned for an injunction. Over the past few years thousands of tenants have been expropriated. There is no clear proof of the advantages of demolition of these old buildings while there are clear signs that the new ones foster crime, overcapacitate infrastructure, do not respond to housing & office space demands (too expensive), and destroy the cultural identity and liveability of the central city areas. Therefore: is it possible to add a marker for endangered building?
closing_comment: No, not in this fashion as this is a tool for errors only.  There is a specific tag for that: https://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:building:condition. This would be the correct way to map such a feature. In case of questions, you are better of asking in one of the forums: forum.osm.org. Cheers, 30303020
